WhatsApp has changed how long you are able to use the “delete for everyone” feature for, The Verge reported. The ability to delete a message after sending it first rolled out during October 2017, and users had 7 minutes to delete a sent message. With the new update, users have 1 hour, 8 minutes, and 16 seconds to delete a message, WABetaInfo found. Commenters pointed out this is 212 seconds. WhatsApp provides the following caveats to deleting messages after they have been sent: